  "prompt": "What is the best time table for a student of maths and science of class 11th?",
  "response": "Creating an effective timetable for a Class 11th student who is studying maths and science involves ensuring a balanced approach to academic and recreational activities. This includes giving adequate time to all subjects, incorporating breaks, and personal interests/hobbies. Here\u2019s a recommended timetable:\n\n### Morning Slot:\n**6:00 AM - 6:30 AM:** Wake up and freshen up\n**6:30 AM - 7:00 AM:** Exercise/meditation\n**7:00 AM - 8:00 AM:** Breakfast and personal time\n**8:00 AM - 9:30 AM:** Study maths (Focus on understanding and solving concepts)\n\n### Late Morning Slot:\n**9:30 AM - 10:00 AM:** Short break (Relax, snack)\n**10:00 AM - 11:30 AM:** Study physics (Focus on theory and problem-solving)\n**11:30 AM - 12:00 PM:** Break (Relax, stretch)\n\n### Afternoon Slot:\n**12:00 PM - 1:30 PM:** Study chemistry (Focus on theory and problem-solving)\n**1:30 PM - 2:30 PM:** Lunch break and relaxation\n\n### Early Evening Slot:\n**2:30 PM - 4:00 PM:** Study optional subjects (if any), or review previously studied maths/science topics\n**4:00 PM - 4:30 PM:** Short break (Relax, snack)\n\n### Evening Slot:\n**4:30 PM - 6:00 PM:** Study practical aspects/projects or revise\n**6:00 PM - 7:00 PM:** Leisure activities (sports, hobbies)\n**7:00 PM - 8:00 PM:** Dinner and family time\n\n### Night Slot:\n**8:00 PM - 9:00 PM:** Revision and homework for the day\n**9:00 PM - 9:30 PM:** Relaxation (Reading, musical activities)\n**9:30 PM:** Prepare for bed\n\n### Weekly Adjustments:\n- **Saturday:** Mock tests and additional problem-solving practice.\n- **Sunday:** Relaxation and light review if necessary.\n\n### Notes:\n1. **Flexibility:** Adjust the timetable as per personal requirements and school schedules.\n2. **Breaks:** Regular short breaks to boost productivity.\n3. **Sleep:** Ensure at least 7-8 hours of sleep.\n4. **Consistency:** Maintain consistency and gradually adjust as per the learning pace and syllabus coverage.\n\nThis timetable ensures a balanced approach to learning maths and science while maintaining mental health and personal growth. Adjust based on upcoming exams, personal pace, and extracurricular commitments.",
